===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰer-}}
Originally a variant of (and hence a doublet of) {{doublet|en|differ|notext=1}}; from {{inh|en|enm|differren|t=to postpone|id=to postpone}}, from {{der|en|fro|differer}}, from {{der|en|la|differō}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|++}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[delay]] or [[postpone]]
#:{{ux|en|We're going to '''defer''' the decision until we have all the facts.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 6-2|IV|vii|141|2|'''Deferre''' the ſpoile of the Citie vntill night:}}
#* {{RQ:Mary Shelley Frankenstein|I|II|65|My journey to Ingolstadt, which had been '''deferred''' by these events, was now again determined upon.}}
## {{lb|en|especially|more common|historically}} to postpone [[induction]] into military service.
# {{lb|en|American football}} After winning the opening [[coin toss]], to [[postpone]] until the start of the second half a team's choice of whether to [[kick off]] or [[receive]] (and to allow the opposing team to make this choice at the start of the first half).
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[delay]], to [[wait]].
#* {{RQ:Milton Paradise Regained|Samson Agonistes|34|lines=474–476|passage=God {{...}} will not long '''defer''' / To vindicate the glory of his name}}

